  "title": "Project Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li><p>Lead the verification of detailed drawings to ensure correct dimensions, orientation, and alignment during project execution</p></li><li><p>Supervise and direct sub-contractors and in-house workers to achieve project milestones and maintain quality standards</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with site operations staff to coordinate activities and meet project schedules effectively</p></li><li><p>Monitor installation processes to ensure adherence to approved drawings and specifications</p></li><li><p>Enforce site safety protocols and ensure all safety requirements are consistently applied</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate and up-to-date site records documenting work progress and report findings to management</p></li><li><p>Plan and allocate manpower and resources strategically to optimize project delivery</p></li><li><p>Prepare and submit Requests for Approval (RFA) and Requests for Information (RFI) with proper documentation, liaising with consultants for approvals and tracking</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with suppliers and material providers to facilitate submissions and owner reviews</p></li><li><p>Assist project management with data tracking and reporting on site work progress</p></li><li><p>Attend project meetings, follow up on issues raised, and support resolution to maintain project momentum</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with project requirements and scope of work throughout project phases</p></li><li><p>Perform additional duties assigned by management to support project success</p></li></ul><p>Job Requirements </p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent) in engineering or related field</p></li><li><p>Four or more years of experience in project management, project engineering, or project planning (scope, schedule, cost, quality)</p></li><li><p>Experience in field management</p></li><li><p>Proficient in AutoCAD and circuit design software to support project documentation and execution</p></li></ul>",
